00:24.940 --> 00:26.960
THE GOSPEL OF MARK

00:26.960 --> 00:29.040
CHAPTER SEVEN

00:29.800 --> 00:33.300
Then came together unto him the Pharisees

00:33.300 --> 00:36.540
and certain of the scribes, which came from Jerusalem.

00:37.080 --> 00:41.000
And when they saw some of his disciples eat bread

00:41.000 --> 00:46.080
with defiled, that is to say, with unwashing hands,

00:46.360 --> 00:47.620
they found fault.

00:47.960 --> 00:50.200
For the Pharisees and all the Jews,

00:50.560 --> 00:55.140
except they wash their hands oft,

00:55.140 --> 00:59.720
eat not, holding the traditions of the elders.

01:00.280 --> 01:03.600
And when they come from the market, except they wash,

01:03.860 --> 01:06.980
they eat not, and many other things there be,

01:07.300 --> 01:11.540
which they have received, to hold as the washing of cups

01:11.540 --> 01:15.220
and pots, brazen vessels and of tables.

01:15.680 --> 01:18.980
Then the Pharisees and scribes asked him,

01:19.380 --> 01:22.480
Why walk not thy disciples according

01:22.480 --> 01:25.220
to the traditions of the elders,

01:25.640 --> 01:28.780
but eat bread with unwashing hands?

01:29.120 --> 01:31.560
He answered and said unto them,

01:31.980 --> 01:35.540
Well, Hathisias prophesied of you hypocrites,

01:35.980 --> 01:39.700
as it is written, this people honoreth me with their lips,

01:40.060 --> 01:42.480
but their hearts are far from me.

01:43.100 --> 01:46.040
Howbeit in vain do they worship me,

01:46.060 --> 01:49.960
teaching for doctrines the commandments of men.

01:50.670 --> 01:53.200
For laying aside the commandment of God,

01:53.540 --> 01:57.160
ye hold the tradition of men as the washing of pots

01:57.160 --> 02:01.240
and cups, and many other such like things ye do.

02:01.560 --> 02:04.640
And he said unto them, full well,

02:05.000 --> 02:07.020
ye reject the commandment of God,

02:07.680 --> 02:09.740
that ye may keep your own tradition.

02:10.440 --> 02:14.700
For Moses said, honor thy father and thy mother,

02:15.080 --> 02:17.800
and whoso curseth, father or mother,

02:17.800 --> 02:20.100
and let him die the death.

02:20.760 --> 02:24.440
But ye say, if a man shall say to his father or mother,

02:24.840 --> 02:27.340
it is Corbin, that is to say a gift,

02:27.700 --> 02:30.540
by whatsoever thou mightest be profited by me,

02:30.860 --> 02:32.180
he shall be free.

02:32.500 --> 02:36.840
And ye suffer him no more to do art for his father

02:36.840 --> 02:41.400
or his mother, making the word of God of non-effect

02:41.400 --> 02:45.060
through your tradition, which ye have delivered,

02:45.060 --> 02:48.440
and many such like things do ye.

02:49.000 --> 02:52.480
And when he had called all the people unto him,

02:52.880 --> 02:56.160
he said unto them, hearken unto me,

02:56.340 --> 02:58.900
every one of you, and understand,

02:59.480 --> 03:02.640
there is nothing from without a man

03:02.640 --> 03:06.020
that entering into him can defile him.

03:06.380 --> 03:09.300
But the things which come out of him,

03:09.420 --> 03:12.820
those are they that defile the man.

03:12.820 --> 03:18.140
If any man have ears to hear, let him hear.

03:18.680 --> 03:23.600
And when he was entered into the house from the people,

03:23.760 --> 03:27.560
his disciples asked him concerning the parable,

03:27.980 --> 03:33.300
and he sayeth unto them, are ye so without understanding also?

03:33.780 --> 03:38.140
Do ye not perceive that whatsoever thing from without

03:38.140 --> 03:41.740
entereth into the man, it cannot defile him,

03:41.740 --> 03:46.500
because it entereth not into his heart, but into the belly,

03:46.920 --> 03:51.340
and goeth out into the draught, purging all meats.

03:52.060 --> 03:56.060
And he said, that which cometh out of the man,

03:56.260 --> 03:59.780
that defileth the man, for from within,

04:00.180 --> 04:03.260
out of the heart of men proceed evil thoughts,

04:03.640 --> 04:08.260
adulteries, fornications, murders, thefts,

04:08.260 --> 04:12.680
covetousness, wickedness, deceit, lasciviousness,

04:12.880 --> 04:17.240
an evil eye, blasphemy, pride, foolishness,

04:17.400 --> 04:22.900
all these evil things come from within and defile the man.

04:23.260 --> 04:27.660
And from thence he arose and went into the borders of Tyre

04:28.130 --> 04:31.520
and Sedan, and entered into in house,

04:31.820 --> 04:36.720
and would have no man know it, but he could not behead.

04:37.180 --> 04:41.280
For a certain woman whose daughter had an unclean spirit

04:41.280 --> 04:44.640
heard of him and came and fell at his feet.

04:45.640 --> 04:49.500
The woman was a Greek, a Syriac Phoenician by nation,

04:49.920 --> 04:53.680
and she besought him that he would cast forth the devil

04:53.680 --> 04:55.040
out of her daughter.

04:55.720 --> 04:59.780
But Jesus said unto her, let the children first be filled,

05:00.180 --> 05:03.200
for it is not me to take the children's bread

05:03.200 --> 05:06.100
and to cast it unto the dogs.

05:06.720 --> 05:10.300
And she answered and said unto him, yes, Lord,

05:10.620 --> 05:14.620
yet the dogs under the table eat of the children's crumbs.

05:15.380 --> 05:19.400
And he said unto her, for this saying, go thy way,

05:19.700 --> 05:22.200
the devil is gone out of thy daughter.

05:22.800 --> 05:25.120
And when she was come to her house,

05:25.500 --> 05:27.500
she found the devil gone out,

05:27.500 --> 05:30.360
and her daughter laid upon the bed.

05:30.760 --> 05:35.440
And again, departing from the coast of Tyre and Sedan,

05:35.440 --> 05:38.480
he came unto the sea of Galilee

05:38.480 --> 05:41.660
through the midst of the coast of Decapolis.

05:41.940 --> 05:45.760
And they bring unto him one that was deaf

05:45.760 --> 05:48.320
and had an impediment in his speech,

05:48.640 --> 05:51.720
and they beseech him to put his hand upon him.

05:51.940 --> 05:55.100
And he took him aside from the multitude

05:55.100 --> 05:57.940
and put his fingers into his ears,

05:58.100 --> 06:01.040
and he spat and touched his tongue.

06:01.300 --> 06:04.760
And looking up to heaven, he sighed,

06:04.760 --> 06:11.400
and saith unto him, ifah, father, that is, be opened.

06:11.840 --> 06:14.240
And straightway his ears were opened,

06:14.600 --> 06:17.260
and the string of his tongue was loosed,

06:17.260 --> 06:18.640
and he spake plain.

06:19.200 --> 06:22.380
And he charged them that they should tell no man,

06:22.800 --> 06:25.620
but the more he charged them so much,

06:25.940 --> 06:29.040
the more a great deal they published it.

06:29.420 --> 06:32.620
And were beyond measure astonished,

06:32.620 --> 06:35.820
saying he hath done all things well,

06:36.380 --> 06:41.040
he maketh both the deaf to hear and the dumb to speak.

06:41.940 --> 06:43.420
Chapter eight.

06:44.760 --> 06:46.420
In those days the multitude,

06:46.780 --> 06:49.640
being very great and having nothing to eat,

06:50.040 --> 06:52.560
Jesus called his disciples unto him,

06:53.000 --> 06:57.880
and saith unto them, I have compassion on the multitude,

06:58.440 --> 07:02.140
because they have now been with me three days,

07:02.140 --> 07:04.160
and have nothing to eat.

07:04.860 --> 07:08.300
And if I send them away fasting to their own houses,

07:08.680 --> 07:10.660
they will faint by the way,

07:11.060 --> 07:14.260
for divers of them came from far.

07:14.720 --> 07:18.140
And his disciples answered him, from whence?

07:18.300 --> 07:22.020
Can a man satisfy these men with bread here

07:22.020 --> 07:23.240
in the wilderness?

07:23.600 --> 07:26.680
And he asked them, how many loaves have ye?

07:27.080 --> 07:28.860
And they said, seven.

07:29.180 --> 07:33.420
And he commanded the people to sit down on the ground,

07:33.760 --> 07:37.100
and he took the seven loaves and gave thanks and break,

07:37.640 --> 07:40.400
and gave to his disciples to set before them.

07:40.640 --> 07:43.480
And they did set them before the people,

07:43.820 --> 07:46.560
and they had a few small fish,

07:46.800 --> 07:51.420
and he blessed and commanded to set them also before them.

07:51.840 --> 07:55.200
So they did eat and were filled,

07:55.200 --> 07:58.160
and they took up of the broken meat

07:58.160 --> 08:01.220
that was left seven baskets.

08:02.100 --> 08:06.480
And they that had eaten were about 4,000,

08:06.700 --> 08:08.940
and he sent them away.

08:09.380 --> 08:13.320
And straightway he entered into a ship with his disciples,

08:13.760 --> 08:18.540
and came into the parts of Doumanutha.

08:18.740 --> 08:23.100
And the Pharisees came forth and began to question with him,

08:23.100 --> 08:27.100
seeking of him a sign from heaven, tempting him.

08:27.920 --> 08:31.160
And he sighed deeply in his spirit and saith,

08:31.540 --> 08:35.200
why doth this generation seek after a sign?

08:35.860 --> 08:39.740
Verily I say unto you, there shall no sign be given

08:39.740 --> 08:41.520
unto this generation.

08:41.840 --> 08:45.400
And he left them, and entering into the ship again,

08:45.700 --> 08:47.960
departed to the other side.

08:48.440 --> 08:51.540
Now the disciples had forgotten to take bread,

08:51.540 --> 08:56.440
neither had they in the ship with them more than one loaf.

08:57.100 --> 08:59.500
And he charged them saying, take heed,

09:00.080 --> 09:03.420
beware of the leaven of the Pharisees

09:03.420 --> 09:05.360
and of the leaven of Herod.

09:05.820 --> 09:08.160
And they reasoned among themselves saying,

09:08.480 --> 09:10.760
it is because we have no bread.

09:11.200 --> 09:14.120
And when Jesus knew it, he saith unto them,

09:14.540 --> 09:17.600
why reason ye because ye have no bread?

09:18.240 --> 09:21.460
Perceive ye not yet, neither understand?

09:22.140 --> 09:24.240
Have ye your heart yet hardened?

09:26.160 --> 09:28.860
Having eyes, see ye not?

09:29.180 --> 09:31.740
And having ears, hear ye not?

09:32.000 --> 09:35.840
And do ye not remember when I break the five loaves

09:35.840 --> 09:40.920
among 5,000, how many baskets full of fragments took ye up?

09:41.340 --> 09:43.640
They say unto him, 12.

09:44.140 --> 09:47.620
And when the seven among 4,000,

09:47.780 --> 09:51.500
how many baskets full of fragments took ye up?

09:51.700 --> 09:53.580
And they said, seven.

09:54.500 --> 09:59.000
And he said unto them, how is it that ye do not understand?

09:59.500 --> 10:02.240
And he cometh to Bethesda,

10:02.340 --> 10:05.060
and they bring a blind man unto him

10:05.060 --> 10:07.360
and besought him to touch him.

10:07.540 --> 10:11.160
And he took the blind man by the hand

10:11.160 --> 10:13.220
and led him out of the town.

10:13.420 --> 10:16.060
And when he had spit on his eyes

10:16.060 --> 10:18.640
and put his hands upon him,

10:18.640 --> 10:21.680
he asked him if he saw art.

10:22.180 --> 10:24.020
And he looked up and said,

10:24.320 --> 10:27.860
I see men as trees walking.

10:28.380 --> 10:32.160
After that, he put his hands again upon his eyes

10:32.160 --> 10:33.960
and made him look up.

10:34.120 --> 10:38.960
He was restored and saw every man clearly.

10:39.700 --> 10:42.740
And he sent him away to his house,

10:42.780 --> 10:45.440
saying, neither go into the town

10:45.440 --> 10:48.680
nor tell it to anyone in the town.

10:49.140 --> 10:51.800
And Jesus went out and his disciples

10:51.800 --> 10:54.920
into the towns of Caesarea Philippi.

10:55.180 --> 10:57.700
And by the way, he asked his disciples,

10:58.220 --> 11:03.220
saying unto them, whom do men say that I am?

11:03.600 --> 11:06.100
And they answered, John the Baptist.

11:06.460 --> 11:11.240
But some say Elias, others one of the prophets.

11:11.780 --> 11:13.460
And he sayeth unto them,

11:13.840 --> 11:16.340
but whom say ye that I am?

11:16.840 --> 11:19.780
And Peter answereth and sayeth unto him,

11:20.140 --> 11:21.940
thou art the Christ.

11:22.380 --> 11:26.520
And he charged them that they should tell no man of him.

11:26.840 --> 11:28.720
And he began to teach them

11:28.720 --> 11:33.000
that the son of man must suffer many things

11:33.000 --> 11:35.640
and be rejected of the elders

11:35.640 --> 11:39.900
and of the chief priests and scribes and be killed.

11:40.460 --> 11:43.700
And after three days rise again.

11:44.200 --> 11:47.540
And he spake that saying openly.

11:48.280 --> 11:51.020
And Peter took him and began to rebuke him.

11:51.320 --> 11:55.340
But when he had turned about and looked on his disciples,

11:55.440 --> 11:58.920
he rebuked Peter, saying, get thee behind me, Satan.

11:59.340 --> 12:01.880
For thou savoreth not the things of God,

12:01.880 --> 12:04.700
but the things that be of men.

12:05.400 --> 12:08.560
And when he had called the people unto him

12:08.560 --> 12:12.300
with his disciples also, he said unto them,

12:12.620 --> 12:14.880
whosoever will come after me,

12:15.220 --> 12:20.180
let him deny himself and take up his cross and follow me.

12:20.500 --> 12:24.400
For whosoever will save his life shall lose it.

12:24.600 --> 12:28.040
But whosoever shall lose his life for my sake

12:28.040 --> 12:31.620
in the gospels, the same shall save it.

12:32.020 --> 12:36.900
For what profit it a man if he shall gain the whole world

12:36.900 --> 12:39.720
and lose his own soul?

12:40.480 --> 12:44.020
Or what shall a man give in exchange for his soul?

12:45.320 --> 12:49.220
Whosoever therefore shall be ashamed of me

12:49.220 --> 12:54.700
and of my words in this adulterous and sinful generation

12:54.700 --> 12:58.580
of him also shall the son of man be ashamed

12:58.580 --> 13:02.080
when he cometh in the glory of his father

13:02.080 --> 13:04.600
with the holy angels.

13:05.820 --> 13:11.140
End of chapter seven and eight of the gospel of Mark.

13:11.960 --> 13:15.320
Recording by Simon Wainwright.

